		   <tr><td class="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform" valign="top" id="forumSubject">Tricks to Twisting<br clear="all" /><script type="text/javascript">document.title = document.title + ": Thread: Tricks to Twisting";</script>
		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Thu, Aug 17th 10:46 PM2000 </span><span id="notbold">| <span class="sm">IP: Logged</span> | <a href="/db/classes.html?class=4&mid=96656681729149&post=1"><a class="sm" href="/db/classes.html?class=4&mid=96656681729149&num=11&page=0&post=1&replyto=96656681729149"><img src="/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif" border="0" alt="Reply..." height="11" width="17" /> Reply to this</a></a>    <a name=96656681729149></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <span id=>Anonymous</span></a><b><span id=></span></b>
		   <br /><nobr><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Good [4.42]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Anonymous&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p><br>Timing is everything with twisting (or Juggling). If you ask most bards they will simply tell you to practice. Well..hmm I don't think that is quite enough. I'll tell you just a few simple tricks that will help greatly.<br><br>1. Use a differant view. Huh you say. Hit F9 twice so that you are using the view from behind yourself.<br><br>From this view you can see the lite show that accompines a song. And IMO the lite show is a split second faster than the "text message".<br><br>During a fight the battle spam can be outrageous! With several caster, /ooc and all the rest it can be easy to miss the "text message" that goes with a song. <br><br>If you are watching the colors of the lite show you dont have to worrie about three groups around you all caster heavy 8 ) Spam'n you out.<br><br>2. HOTKEYS!!! I can't explain to you the importance of making your songs and certain inventory slots into hotkeys.<br><br>Let me explain to you how to make a "gem" (song or spell) hotkey'd. Hit F10 until you are at the screen where you have the pretty borders. LOL<br><br>Left-Click and hold down on a song on the left hand side of your screen. You will see it attach it self to your cursor. Simply place it in a hotkey slot. <br><br>Now when you hit #1 on the keyboard that song starts, hit it again and it stops, hit #2 and song #2 starts...keep this up and you are twisting!!!! 8-0&nbsp;&nbsp;hehe<br><br>3. This next bit will help alot with switching weapons and instuments! You also need to be able to do this quickly. This is a bit more diffuclut, but it can be done.<br><br>Make Hotkeys for both your primary and seconday weapon slots. Then dedicate 4 inventory slot to hotkeys as well. (This can be done with 3 but I like 4). Now to switch a weapon for an instrument it is all done on the same screen you are using and you dont have to hit "I" to go to full inventory.<br><br>Why you ask? Just imagine seeing your two partners in the group get crushed by that wondering RED Necro caster (ouchie) what can u do?! RUN RUN RUN. <br><br>Hit #1 (it is always my Selo) Hit Shift 1 (as you are already running, move the weapons to to inventory slots and that beautiful drum in to place...Zoooommmmmmm <br><br>You have lived to sing another day....your next song will most likey be "locating corpse song"  hehe<br><br>I hope this helps a little. If it does let me know. If you think it sux, keep that to yourself...LOL Just Kidding what ever you think of it let me know....<br><br>Klipso Dis`Kordant<br>Bards of Norrath<br>Rodcet Nife<br><br>eqklipso@hotmail.com<br></p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8"></td><td align="right" id="fs8" >11 Replies</td></tr></table>
