		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform2" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=209701"><span id=>harjared</span></a><b><span id=></span></b><br />25 posts
		   <br /><nobr><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=harjared&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p>In group I like to manually twist my four songs.&nbsp;&nbsp;This way I can quickly switch songs if needed, as well as deal with missed notes.  But when chant kiting, whether I am just finishing off a swarm kited mob or having chant kited the whole kill, I have some custom hotkeys set up.  I put my 4 DoT songs in the top 4 spell slots.  I then make 2 hotkeys:<br><br>Hotkey 1<br><br>/stop song<br>/cast 1<br>/pause 27 (equals 2.7 seconds, or whatever cast duration of song is, 30 for 3 seconds 29 for 2.9 etc.)<br>/stop song<br>/cast 2<br><br>Hotkey 2<br><br>/stop song<br>/cast 3<br>/pause 27<br>/stop song<br>/cast 4<br><br>Then I usually key these 2 hotkeys to my + and - keys on my number pad and alternately cycle them.  This way I can chant kite without getting carpal tunnel.  Yes missed notes do happen, but I just continue on, they still die.<br><br>Yzuki 61 Bard Stromm<br><br>&quot;....and one time at Bard camp, I put my Troubador's Mace up my ass&quot;<br><br><i><span class="sm">Edited, Fri Jul 23 01:50:36 2004 by harjared</span class="sm"></i></p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8"></td><td align="right" id="fs8" >0 Replies</td></tr></table>
