		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform2" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=230592"><span id=>esoterique</span></a><b><span id=></span></b><br />30 posts
		   <br /><nobr><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Default [2.27]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=esoterique&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p>A few very good tips - I generally prefer not to look at the light show - partivularly once you get to raiding levels, this can cause lag, and be hard to follow at times. I follow the casting bar, personally. As for hotkeys - I prefer to manually twist, due to missed notes, and the fact that I tend to adapt my twist based on what is going on - if I see that someone can't land a slow, I will start twisting Occlusion of Sound, and throw on a Requiem of Time, to tide the group over until a slow lands. Again - it's all preferance. Many bards prefer hotkeys, many prefer the flexibility of manual twisting. It's all in play styles.</p><br /><span class="sm">----------------------------</span><br />--Arianea Rhapsody</td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8"></td><td align="right" id="fs8" >0 Replies</td></tr></table>
