		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=247125"><span id=Scholar>Jiggidyjay of the Seven Seas</span></a><b><span id=Scholar><br>Scholar</span></b><br /><img alt="Avatar" height="73" width="100" src="/uf/Jiggidyjay/Avatar2.jpg"><br /><br /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*"/><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><br />1340 posts
		   <br /><nobr><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Good [4.18]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Jiggidyjay&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>I'm an oldschool double-tapper too. I never use the effects for timing, and very rarely the casting bar. The slightest bit of lag can delay your twist enough to cause songs to start dropping if you're depending on the casting bar. By the time you reach the 30's or 40's, you should have the timing down pretty good anyway, but it is a good idea to watch the bar until you get the rythm. One thing to remember when watching the bar is that you can end a song JUST before it casts according to the casting bar. Using this timing you will eventually be able to sustain a 4 song twist relatively easily (as long as the computer and connection is being kind). I'm able to sustain a 4 song twist relatively reliably in BoT and WoS, except for those times I get like 4 missed notes in a row.<br><br>They key is to get to the point where you can time your twisting blindfolded. This allows you to pay attention to what's going on around you instead of the casting bar all the time, which is an immensely valuable skill when you're called on to be crowd control.</p><br /><span class="sm">----------------------------</span><br /><a href="HTTP://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1006062" target="akztarg">Jiggidyjay</a> - <span class="sm">Mr Ranger</span class="sm"><br><a href="HTTP://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1003866" target="akztarg">Zingin Ansinging</a> - <span class="sm">Mr Bard of <a href="HTTP://firestormers.com/viewnews.php" target="akztarg">The Firestormers</a></span class="sm"><br><a href="HTTP://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1006061" target="akztarg">Zolotaya</a> - <span class="sm">Ms Necro</span class="sm"><br><br>&lt;--- 1k post, non-contributing n00b</td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8">Posting from the Oval Office.</td><td align="right" id="fs8" >0 Replies</td></tr></table>
